goals.question: What is the trend of the opening price over time?
goals.visualization: Line chart of the opening price against time
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify if the opening price is increasing, decreasing or remaining constant over time.

goals.question: What is the average daily trading volume?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of the daily trading volume
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify the average daily trading volume and if there are any spikes or dips in the volume.

goals.question: What is the correlation between the closing price and the volume?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of the closing price against the volume
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify if there is any correlation between the closing price and the volume. A positive correlation indicates that as the volume increases, the closing price also increases.

goals.question: What is the distribution of the daily high and low prices?
goals.visualization: Box plot of the daily high and low prices
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify the range and distribution of the daily high and low prices. It also helps to identify any outliers in the data.

goals.question: What is the average daily return?
goals.visualization: Line chart of the daily return against time
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify the average daily return and if there are any spikes or dips in the return. A positive return indicates that the stock is performing well.

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['open'])
    plt.xlabel('Time')
    plt.ylabel('Opening Price')
    plt.title('What is the trend of the opening price over time?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data = data.set_index('date')
    daily_volume = data['volume']
    avg_daily_volume = daily_volume.mean()
    
    ax = daily_volume.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.axhline(y=avg_daily_volume, color='r', linestyle='-', label=f'Average: {avg_daily_volume:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the average daily trading volume?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='ignore')
    data.boxplot(column=['High', 'Low'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title("What is the distribution of the daily high and low prices?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data['daily_return'] = data['close'].pct_change()
    data['daily_return'].plot(kind='line')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.axhline(data['daily_return'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Average: {data['daily_return'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the average daily return?")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
